# Environment variables for this .NET service. Copy to .env and fill in.
# Only this .env.example is committed - real .env* files are gitignored.
# Read these from the environment (12-factor); never hard-code or commit secrets.
#
# `.env.schema` is the contract these variables must match, and `make check`
# fails if this file and the schema drift apart. When you add a variable, declare
# it in both places.
#
# .NET binds `__` (double underscore) to nested config sections, so
# ConnectionStrings__Default maps to ConnectionStrings:Default.

# --- Runtime ---
ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT=Development
# URLs Kestrel binds to. Inside a container bind to all interfaces, e.g.
# ASPNETCORE_URLS=http://+:8080
# Some platforms inject PORT instead; map it into ASPNETCORE_URLS yourself.
# PORT=8080

# --- Database (uncomment if the service uses one) ---
# ConnectionStrings__Default=Host=localhost;Port=5432;Database=app;Username=app;Password=app

# --- Auth / third-party secrets (uncomment as needed) ---
# Jwt__Secret=
# ApiKey=
